    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Same issue, 681 MiB available memory, genesis.json->difficulty=0, yet each block takes ~2-30 minutes to mine.  Waiting over the weekend for adjustments to take place results in no noticeable improvement.\r\n\r\nOnly solution that has yet to work has been to do:\r\n\r\n`git clone --branch v1.8.13 ... https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum.git`\r\n`sed -i 's/return CalcDifficulty(chain.Config(), time, parent)/return big.NewInt(2)/' ./go-ethereum/consensus/ethash/consensus.go`\r\n`cd ./go-ethereum && make geth`\r\n\r\nby recompiling geth with a forced difficulty of \"2\", blocks now commit at a ridiculous rate of one block per second.\r\n\r\nConclusions:\r\n\r\n- my platform is more than capable of mining blocks at a fast rate (thus memory is NOT the problem)\r\n- geth has a serious bug in difficulty calculations\r\n",
